rd.com/ugladriellumenaura.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gladriel Lumenaura</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/3/02 4:29:49 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: INT vs. CHA vs. AC vs. HP</span><hr size=1> I'm sure someone will post some helpful maths on this, although it's above me and I'm not much interested in it - my personal view is that no stat matters as much as skill. High INT won't make up for poor mana management, high AC and HP won't make up for poor aggro management / lack of slows. As for CHA, well I still find I can mez just as easily nekkid on a CR as I can fully clothed.<br>
<br>
My stats are average I guess, 229 INT, 209 CHA, 700+AC and 1700+HP, people who raid a lot are probably have much higher than this.<br>
<br>
And although the Kromif leggings are very good, Leggings of the Astral are also worth considering, especially if you are pursuing INT... highest in the game I believe with 7ac and 10 INT... I wouldn't trade my pair for anything. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utilien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tilien</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/3/02 4:55:50 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/strider636/myhomepage/fire4%20-%20gif%202.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: INT vs. CHA vs. AC vs. HP</span><hr size=1> They didn't fully remove the soft cap at 200 - just changed it. Before, you used to get 1 mana for every INT point above 200. Now you get 6 mana. Below 200 INT, at 60, you get 12 mana per point.<br>
<br>
It makes additional INT more useful, but hardly neccesary. I certainly wouldn't worry about swapping out mana items for INT in a hurry since the gain is minimal in most cases - in fact, in some slots and with some mana items, you'd lose mana overall.<br>
<br>
I'd just take it as a matter of opportunity. Not too hard to do the math (you get a new item that gives you 8 INT for a slot where you've already got a 50 mana item. 8x6=48.) <p><a href="http://www.mithrilweb.com" target="_blank">
<img src="http://members.aol.com/strider636/MW_Sigs/Tilsig.jpg" border="0">
</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uulaian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulaian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Whore</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/3/02 6:37:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: INT vs. CHA vs. AC vs. HP</span><hr size=1> Maintaining good AC/HP seems easily more important to me than maxing out int/cha. Simply put, for normal grouping the big factor isn't your total mana pool, but rather how fast you regenerate your mana. And enchanters have it easy in that area, never being without clarity, and with ToT when around casting mobs. So at most times, you're more likely to die from dropping too fast for heals to land, than from running out of mana. I'd wager one could get by just fine with a fairly low int, actually, as the size of the mana pool is a non-factor as long as you regen fast enough not to exhaust it. <p>Ulaian Moonleaf <BR>
-Warder <BR>
Dark Whispers</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uakbarbelakesh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akbar BelAkesh</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/3/02 9:31:12 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: INT vs. CHA vs. AC vs. HP</span><hr size=1> What Ulaian said.<br>
